Arnold Schwarzenegger

Arnold Schwarzenegger detained at Munich airport over luxury watch

Criminal proceedings initiated against Hollywood actor for allegedly failing to declare plans to sell watch

AFP in Munich
Wed 17 Jan 2024 12.36 ESTFirst published on Wed 17 Jan 2024 12.33 EST

The Hollywood actor Arnold Schwarzenegger has been held at Munich airport for allegedly failing to declare an expensive watch he was planning to sell.

The Austrian-born actor and former governor of California, 76, was detained in the customs area of the airport on Wednesday afternoon after arriving in Germany from the US, said a customs spokesperson, Thomas Meister.

Schwarzenegger was expected to be able to continue his journey later in the day but the watch will probably have to stay, Meister said.

Criminal proceedings were initiated against the Terminator star and former bodybuilding icon for tax evasion, he said. Tax should have been paid on the watch because Schwarzenegger was intending to sell it in the EU, according to Meister.

The luxury timepiece was due to be auctioned at a fundraising dinner for Schwarzeneggers climate initiative in the Austrian ski resort of Kitzbhel on Thursday, the German newspaper Bild daily reported.

Items typically auctioned at such dinners include works of art and signed memorabilia, according to the initiatives website.

The timepiece was made especially for Schwarzenegger by the luxury Swiss watchmaker Audemars Piguet, according to Bild.
